OBJC_SYSVAR

Purpose:	Set or inquire object-related global system variables

Parameters:	control[0]  = 48
		control[1]  = 3
		control[2]  = 2
		control[3]  = 0
		control[4]  = 0

		int_in[0]   = ob_svmode
		int_in[1]   = ob_svwhich
		int_in[2]   = ob_svinval2
		int_in[3]   = ob_svinval1

		int_out[0]  = ob_svreturn
		int_out[1]  = ob_svoutval1
		int_out[2]  = ob_svoutval2


		ob_svmode	- A code to identify set or inquiry.
				  0 - inquire
				  1 - set

				
		ob_svwhich	- A code to identify which system variable.
				  1 - LK3DIND - look of 3D indicators
				  2 - LK3DACT - look of 3D action objects
				  3 - INDBUTCOL  - indicator button color
				  4 - ACTBUTCOL  - activator button color
				  5 - ALRTCOL - alert background color


		ob_svinval1	- A value to set to.

				  When ob_svwhich is LK3DIND:
				  -1 - do not change the current value
					of 3D indicators
				   0 - do not animate text of 3D indicators
				   1 - animate text of 3D indicators

				  When ob_svwhich is LK3DACT:
				  -1 - do not change the text orientation
					of 3D activators
				   0 - do not animate text of 3D activators
				   1 - animate text of 3D activators
				  

				  When ob_svwhich is INDBUTCOL, ACTBUTCOL
				  or ALRTCOL:
				  - A color number to set the color of the 
				    indicator button, the activator button
				    or the alert background respectively.


		ob_svinval2	- A value to set to.

				  When ob_svwhich is LK3DIND:
				  -1 - do not change the current value
				   0 - do not change the face color of the
					3D indicators when selected
				   1 - change the face color of the
					3D indicators when selected

				  When ob_svwhich is LK3DACT:
				  -1 - do not change the current value
				   0 - do not change the face color of the
					3D activators when selected
				   1 - change the face color of the
					3D activators when selected
				  

		ob_svreturn	  0 - an error exists
				  n (positive integer) - no error exists


		ob_svoutval1	  When ob_svwhich is LK3DIND:
				   0 - if text is not animated on 3D
					indicators
				   1 - if text is animated on 3D indicators

				  When ob_svwhich is LK3DACT:
				   0 - if text is not animated on 3D
					activators
				   1 - if text is animated on 3D activators

				  When ob_svwhich is INDBUTCOL, ACTBUTCOL
				  or ALRTCOL:
				   - the current color of the indicator
					button, the activator button or the
					alert background.

		ob_svoutval2	  When ob_svwhich is LK3DIND:
				   0 - if face color of the 3D indicators
					will not be changed when selected
				   1 - if face color of the 3D indicators
					will be changed when selected

				  When ob_svwhich is LK3DACT:
				   0 - if face color of the 3D activators
					will not be changed when selected
				   1 - if face color of the 3D activators
					will be changed when selected



Sample call to C language binding:

ob_svreturn = objc_xtend(ob_svmode, ob_svwhich, ob_svinval1, ob_svinval2,
		&ob_svoutval1, &ob_svoutval2);

